gpu_resources.notes: CLUSTERS INCLUDED + CALCULATIONS: 1) AI Makerspace (Student Dedicated): 20 nodes × 8 H100 GPUs/node = 160 H100 SXM (HGX H100 systems). 2) Phoenix Cluster (Research/HPC): 12 nodes × 2 A100 80GB (24 total), 4 nodes × 2 A100 40GB (8 total), 80 V100s (mixed 32/16GB), and 56 RTX 6000s. 3) ICE Cluster (Instructional): 32 T4s. analysis_notes: Ensemble result aggregated from OpenAI, Claude, and Gemini models. Georgia Tech possesses a significant dedicated 'AI Makerspace' for students featuring 160 H100s, distinct from standard research clusters. Student enrollment figures are heavily skewed by the large OMSCS program.
